page.title: 05EAST CAWLEDGE WOOD.
page.content: In{East Cawledge Wood,}in the north west corner of our block,there were some animal tracks.We were able to identify fox and deer tracks.We also saw a{fallow deer}and several birds. We identified these birds as thrushes, starlings,pigeons,rooks,merlins, chaffinches,blackbirds and sparrows. At the edge of the wood,we also identified some house martins. In the wood we saw various{flowers, and identified wild garlic,blue bells,violets,dogs mercury,tufted vetch,butter cups and dandelions.There is a stream running through the forest called{Cawledge Burn.}
